M.G.L. c. 186 (Landlord & Tenant statute.proposition: Under Massachusetts common law, every tenancy includes an implied and/or express covenant of quiet enjoyment whereby the landlord is obligated to ensure that the tenant’s possession and enjoyment of the premises will not be substantially and unreasonably disturbed by the landlord or persons for whom the landlord is legally responsible.
